    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d2fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-20">20 March
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 506. Personal and secret. From the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p>I am very angry with myself. The old attack of grippe having hung on and on,
                    leaving me with an intermittent temperature, Ross<note n="2" xml:id="d2fn2">Vice
                        Admiral Ross T. McIntire, Roosevelt’s physician.</note> decided about a week
                    ago that it is necessary for me to take a complete rest <pb facs="0058" n="4"
                        xml:id="pg_4"/> of about two or three weeks in a suitable climate which I am
                    definitely planning to do beginning at the end of this month. I see no way out
                    and I am furious.</p>
                <p>It will therefore be impossible for me to get to a staff meeting in early April.
                    I believe that such a meeting on the Teheran scale in early April would be most
                    useful and if you agree I will send my Chiefs of Staff to Bermuda for that
                    purpose at any time that suits your convenience.</p>
                <p>I am glad you feel hardened about <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss>. Its accomplishment may synchronize with a real Russian
                    break-through.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
